JOHANNESBURG – Three people have been injured after a truck crashed into #BlackMonday protesters following a thirteen-vehicle collision on the N4, outside of Middleburg in Mpumalanga. There is a series of marches by farmers who are protesting against the rise of farm murders in the country. IN PICTURES: #BlackMonday protests gain momentum ER24 spokesperson, Russel Meiring said: “Paramedics found that ten vehicles and three trucks were completely blocking the entire one side of the road. Several vehicles were found overturned on the grassy embankment.” Meiring said traffic police officers had to close off the road and divert the traffic while paramedics assessed the patients. “It is understood that a driver of a truck apparently lost control, causing the vehicle to crash into several others during an apparent protest action,” he added. eNCA